    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static SffParser create(File sffFile)
                        throws FileNotFoundException
        Create a new instance of SffParser that will parse the given sff encoded file. The file isn't actually parsed until one of the accept methods is called.
        Parameters:
        sffFile - the sff file to parse
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if sffFile is null.
        FileNotFoundException - if sffFile does not exist.

      • create

        public static SffParser create(InputStream inputStream)
                        throws FileNotFoundException
        Create a new instance of SffParser that will parse the given sff encoded InputStream. Please Note that inputStream implementations of the FastaFileParser can not create SffVisitorCallback.SffVisitorMementos or use #accept(SffVisitor, SffVisitorMemento). The InputStream isn't actually parsed until one of the SffFileParser#accept(SffVisitor) is called.
        Parameters:
        inputStream - an InputStream that contains sff encoded data to be parsed; can not be null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if sffFile is null.
        FileNotFoundException - if sffFile does not exist.

      • accept

        protected void accept(InputStream in,
                      SffVisitor visitor)
               throws IOException
        Parse the given InputStream containing sff encoded data and call the appropriate visitXXX methods on the given visitor.
        Parameters:
        in - InputStream containing sff encoded data
        visitor - the visitor to visit.
        Throws:
        SffDecoderException - if there is a problem parsing the sff data.
        NullPointerException - if the inputstream or visitor are null.
        IOException
